Risk Rating Interpretation
0
1-5: Low Risk (Manage with routine controls)
0
6-10: Medium Risk (Implement additional controls where practicable)
•
12-15: High Risk (Action required to reduce risk)
•
16-25: Very High Risk (Work must not proceed until risk is reduced)
Key Principles for Use
0
Apply consistent judgement when assigning scores
0
•
Consider existing control measures before scoring residual risk
Use the matrix as a decision-support tool—not a substitute for professional
judgement
Ensure alignment with site-specific risk criteria where applicable
10. Hierarchy of Control
The hierarchy of control provides a structured approach to reducing risk:
1. Elimination
2. Substitution
3. Engineering Controls
4. Administrative Controls
5. Personal Protective Equipment (PPE)
Effective risk management prioritises higher-level controls wherever reasonably
practicable.
